
Javascript is more than rotating text and AJAX callbacks. It is a language that is gaining in popularity and programmers. Every developer needs Javascript on the resume. It is time to take Javascript seriously.

Gone (almost) are the days of fighting browser bugs (Modernizer) and stepping on language landmines. With ECMAScript 5 ("use strict";), JSLint and simplifying your language features:

Javascript has become cool! <Dr Who in a Stetson>

Javascript is a wonderful language composed of objects, functions and landmines.

While objects and landmines are important. Functions are the very best part of Javascript. They are almost perfect and mostly misunderstood. Today I am talking about functions.

If you already understand the brilliance of lexical scope, function scope, hoisting, closures, and curring, you might be in the wrong room.

Lets start with a quiz.

